# Payments Domain Standard (Stripe)

## Purpose

Define how Stripe is integrated for payment processing in the enterprise e-commerce platform.

Payments context owns payment records and Stripe communication — not order fulfillment logic.

---

## Architecture

```
┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐
│   Checkout  │────▶│  Payments   │────▶│   Stripe    │
│   (session) │     │  Service    │     │    API      │
└─────────────┘     └──────┬──────┘     └──────┬──────┘
                           │                    │
                    ┌──────▼──────┐     ┌──────▼──────┐
                    │  Payment    │◀────│  Webhooks   │
                    │  Records    │     │  Handler    │
                    └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘
```

Webhook handler validates signature, deduplicates events, delegates to domain services.

---

## PCI Scope Reduction

### Allowed

- Stripe Payment Element / Checkout (SAQ A)
- Store `payment_intent_id`, `charge_id`, last4, brand, exp_month/year
- Store Stripe customer ID

### Forbidden

- Raw card numbers (PAN)
- CVV/CVC
- Magnetic stripe data
- Custom card input fields

All card data flows directly to Stripe via Elements.

See `security/02-pci` for full compliance requirements.

