## Anti-Patterns

- Business logic only in webhook handler without domain service
- Trusting client-side payment success without webhook confirmation
- Processing webhooks without signature verification
- Storing Stripe secret key in frontend
- Creating multiple PaymentIntents for same checkout without idempotency
- Double order placement on webhook retry without dedup
- Synchronous Stripe calls inside DB transactions
- Logging full webhook payloads with PII in production

